      "content": "that's a good point about the ISRs. i'll double check if we're accidentally hitting the heap during any interrupt-driven tasks. \n\none more thing—it's really frustrating because these spikes feel so disconnected from the actual logic. it feels like something is just \"sneaking\" into the memory and staying there, almost like it's intentionally hiding in the gaps between our standard logging intervals. are there any specific patterns or \"signatures\" I should look for that indicate a leak is being caused by something more complex than just a missing free?",
